ilms, and how they relate to her female-centred perspective.Key featuresExamines how the director's filmic innovations create a sensorial space for the female experience to be expressedBuilds on recent work on film as a multisensory mediumCovers Duras's entire film production, including short films and early adaptations  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMotion pictureszFrancexHistory. 0aWomen motion picture producers and directorszFrance. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831107804200 cprintz978147444054740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474427869zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474427869zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474427869/original  a978-3-11-078042-0 Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA